h done? He come by an\'92 he got on white pants. An\'92 he says, \'91Come on, le\'92s go out to my yacht.\'92 By God, I\'92ll whang him some day!\'94 He breathed heavily. \'93I ain\'92t been out with a woman sence I los\'92 my eye. An\'92 he says stu like that.\'94 And big tears cut channels in the dirt beside his nose. Tom said impatiently, \'93Whyn\'92t you roll on? Got no guards to keep ya here.\'94 \'93Yeah, that\'92s easy to say. Ain\'92t so easy to get a job\'97not for a oneeye\'92 man.\'94 Tom turned on him. \'93Now look-a-here, fella. You got that eye wide open. An\'92 ya dirty, ya stink. Ya jus\'92 askin\'92 for it. Ya like it. Lets ya feel sorry for yaself. \'92Course ya can\'92t get no woman with that empty eye appin\'92 aroun\'92. Put somepin over it an\'92 wash ya face. You ain\'92t hittin\'92 nobody with no pipe wrench.\'94 \'93I tell ya, a one-eye\'92 fella got a hard row,\'94 the man said. \'93Can\'92t see stu the way other fellas can. Can\'92t see how far o a thing is. Ever\'92thing\'92s jus\'92 at.\'94 Tom said, \'93Ya full a crap. Why, I knowed a one-legged whore one time. Think she was takin\'92 two-bits in a alley? No, by God! She\'92s gettin\'92 half a dollar extra. She says, \'91How many one-legged women you slep\'92 with? None!\'92 she says. \'91O.K.,\'92 she says. \'91You got somepin pretty special here, an\'92 it\'92s gonna cos\'92 ya half a buck extry.\'92 An\'92 by God, she was gettin\'92 \'92em, too, an\'92 the fellas comin\'92 out thinkin\'92 they\'92re pretty lucky. She says she\'92s good luck. An\'92 I knowed a humpback in\'97in a place I was. Make his whole livin\'92 lettin\'92 folks rub his hump for luck. Jesus Christ, an\'92 all you got is one eye gone.\'94 The man said stumblingly, \'93Well, Jesus, ya see somebody edge away from ya, an\'92 it gets into ya.\'94 \'93Cover it up then, goddamn it. Ya stickin\'92 it out like a cow\'92s ass. Ya like to feel sorry for yaself. There ain\'92t nothin\'92 the matter with you. Buy yaself some