em? No, sir.\'94 \'93Well, what is?\'94 Jule asked. \'93I\'92ll tell ya. It\'92s \'92cause we\'92re all a-workin\'92 together. Depity can\'92t pick on one fella in this camp. He\'92s pickin\'92 on the whole darn camp. An\'92 he don\'92t dare. All we got to do is give a yell an\'92 they\'92s two hunderd men out. Fella organizin\'92 for the union was a-talkin\'92 out on the road. He says we could do that any place. Jus\'92 stick together. They ain\'92t raisin\'92 hell with no two hunderd men. They\'92re pickin\'92 on one man.\'94 \'93Yeah,\'94 said Jule, \'93an\'92 suppose you got a union? You got to have leaders. They\'92ll jus\'92 pick up your leaders, an\'92 where\'92s your union?\'94 \'93Well,\'94 said Willie, \'93we got to gure her out some time. I been out here a year, an\'92 wages is goin\'92 right on down. Fella can\'92t feed his fam\'92ly on his work now, an\'92 it\'92s gettin\'92 worse all the time. It ain\'92t gonna do no good to set aroun\'92 an\'92 starve. I don\'92 know what to do. If a fella owns a team a horses, he don\'92t raise no hell if he got to feed \'92em when they ain\'92t workin\'92. But if a fella got men workin\'92 for him, he jus\'92 don\'92t give a damn. Horses is a hell of a lot more worth than men. I don\'92 understan\'92 it.\'94 \'93Gets so I don\'92 wanta think about it,\'94 said Jule. \'93An\'92 I got to think about it. I got this here little girl. You know how purty she is. One week they give her a prize in this camp \'92cause she\'92s so purty. Well, what\'92s gonna happen to her? She\'92s gettin\'92 spindly. I ain\'92t gonna stan\'92 it. She\'92s so purty. I\'92m gonna bust out.\'94 \'93How?\'94 Willie asked. \'93What you gonna do\'97steal some stu an\'92 git in jail? Kill somebody an\'92 git hung?\'94 \'93I don\'92 know,\'94 said Jule. \'93Gits me nuts thinkin\'92 about it. Gets me clear nuts.\'94 \'93I\'92m a-gonna miss them dances,\'94 Tom said. \'93Them was some of the nicest dances I ever seen. Well, I\'92m gonna turn in. So l