\'93No. I\'92ll have it right here. And I want a boiled egg and a piece of cinnamon toast. Four and a half minutes on the egg. Make sure. I don\'92t want it gooey.\'94 \
\'93You must feel better, ma\'92am.\'94 \
\'93I do,\'94 she said. \'93That new medicine is wonderful. You look dragged by dogs, Joe. Don\'92t you feel well?\'94 \
\'93I\'92m all right,\'94 he said and set the tray on the table in front of the big deep chair. \'93Four and a half minutes?\'94 \
\'93That\'92s right. And if there\'92s a good apple\'97a crisp apple \'97bring that too.\'94 \
\'93You ain\'92t et like this since I knew you,\'94 he said. \
