Back in her room he said, \'93Didn\'92t have no apples. He said this was a good pear.\'94 \
\'93I\'92d like that even better,\'94 said Kate. \
He watched her chip off the egg and dip a spoon into the shell. \'93How is it?\'94 \
\'93Perfect!\'94 said Kate. \'93Just perfect.\'94 \
\'93You look good,\'94 he said. \
\'93I feel good. You look like hell. What\'92s the matter?\'94 \
Joe went into it warily. \'93Ma\'92am, there ain\'92t nobody needs five hundred like I do.\'94 \
She said playfully, \'93There isn\'92t anyone who needs\'97\'94 \'93What?\'94 \
\'93Forget it. What are you trying to say? You couldn\'92t find her\'97is that it? Well, if you did a good job looking, you\'92ll get your five hundred. Tell me about it.\'94 She picked up the salt shaker and scattered a few grains into the open eggshell. \
